<br>
For the most part people are great. Most I find not only sign up nice and early, but they actually read the instructions and print out the maps!  For those that are not so great, I have a tip, as raid leader invest in a couple of potions. If a person presents enough of a problem, in tells suggest that they may wish to take a graceful exit, and provide them with a way out. &lt; A less expensive way would be a wizard to TL if available&gt;.<br>
<br>
Another tip, from Valquiss, instead of camping out to chat channels, have people make a character of a similar name on another server, and when they camp out, they can log on this character and /join firiona:raidchannel.  You would not believe how much nicer this is for the raid leader <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One other thought ....As a raid leader you also owe the folk who have taken the time to attend something. If a critical class does not come to the raid, or the mob you seek is not up, respect the time and commitment of your friends. Offer the chance of an alternate activity hopefully close for those who choose to stay. Of course if you change the aim of the raid also allow folk the option to do other things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
